Does ANC work when wired? No, ANC can't be turned on in wired mode. But it works whether Bluetooth is on or off Why the Bluetooth can't be turned on? Please fully charge your headphone with USB-A to USB-C charging cable and a 5-10W power wall charger (don't use fast charger). Then reset it.Please use headphone within the operating temperature range: 0°C (32 F) - 45°C(113 F) Can I use AUX when out of battery? Yes, when the NC95 Over-ear headphone is out of battery, you can still listen to music but ANC mode is unavailable. Can I adjust the volume on my headphones in wired mode? No, the mic and volume button controls do not work in wired mode. How to reset the headphones? 1. Fully charge headphones with the original charging cable and 5-10w charger (do not use fast charger). 2. Insert the included audio cable into the headphone and then remove it (You may have to insert it a few times to reset successfully).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewText: 1. The green color is soooooo perfect!2. Great looking and quality feeling dupes. I personally prefer this look the the Apple. The headband looks better.3. The controls print on the headset is amazing. Answer and end calls, pause skip and start music, volume up and down and turning the anc noise cancelling in and off without needing your phone is amazing!4. Sound isn’t 10/10 but it’s still 9/10 personally I think it’s perfectly great for $65. If anything I could describe it has “the bass and subwoofer is a little too high compared to the voices and instruments” if that makes sense. But I’d rather have more bass than not enough so it’s a win for me!5.The noise cancelling WORKS! I ran my sink while resting the modes and it works so well to dim it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars You get what you paid for!
reviews.reviewText: These are knock offs, but for $80. They honestly do the job. The noise cancellation works, but is more better and effective when music is playing. The transparency mode is pretty effective, but it’s not crisp. They’re very comfortable to wear for a long time and glasses safe. However, sound does leak through when you put the volume halfway loud. The battery life seems to go down every hour and 30 minutes. The headphones come with a aux cord so you can plug your headphones into your phone or a computer without using Bluetooth. Overall I think it’s worth the money if you like the sleek design and want some nice headphones with good quality sound that aren’t $599 these are your go to!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Surprisingly awesome for price
reviews.reviewText: These headphones are surprisingly awesome. I was rather impressed with the quality considering the price. They are easy to pair, came charged & super cute. People have actually asked me if they were the Airmax Pros ! I also really like how you can pause/skip & adjust the volume on the headphones (which many headphones lack). Noise cancelling are pretty good. I can’t hear very much when I play music. When there’s no music, they still cancel a lot but not everything, like most headphones. I do wish they could get a little louder but still great sound quality. 4.5/5

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So far so good!
reviews.reviewText: My AirPods were dying and weren’t keeping a charge. I purchased these as a quick fix before getting more expensive ones but these one are actually really decent! The sound is great and they connect very easily to my devices. They feel super sturdy and I was able to wear them for an 8 hour work day without any discomfort. They’re comfy and look good too! For an inexpensive pair of headphones these are great!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Have had so many people already ask me where I’ve gotten these cause they’re so cute! Besides the look, I’ve had them for about a month and the battery has lasted so long on one single charge. Quality is great and you can tell the difference between the transparency mode and noise canceling. It’s not completely noise canceling but for the price, totally worth it. Very comfortable too. I have a smaller head and these stay on well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: There are so much I want to say about these headphones, but I don’t even know where to start. They are exactly like the AirPod max dupes. They are so soft and comfortable on the ear. I have a bunch of ear piercings and I can’t wear your buds, so these were such a great alternative. The ear hole is big enough to wear your whole ear fits and it’s snug and comfortable and super soft and honestly lightweight. You don’t even realize that you have on that phones like these are amazing. Amazing.!!!!!!!!!😻

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Broke after 19 days
reviews.reviewText: These are a great apple dupe without the insane price. Super noise cancelling. Still pretty slim and sleek compared to other dupes. HOWEVER, they broke after 19 days. I was listening one day and randomly the sound gets staticky then the sound went out as a whole. I would try to turn off and back on and it sounds like a staticky glitch noise where it sounds like it’s trying to turn on but just doesn’t. Really annoying they broke so soon but I loved them so much that I’m exchanging the broken ones to get a new pair. Ain’t nobody got $550 to buy real apple headphones….beggars can’t be choosers 🤷🏼‍♀️

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A little too big for my tiny head
reviews.reviewText: Had these headphones for a little over 24 hours. They came almost fully charged which was nice. The sound quality is pretty good (can't say too much since my last headphones were $10 from the drugstore). Doesn't cancel noise 100% unless you crank the volume up, but I don't mind since I like to hear a bit of my surroundings in public. They are very comfortable on even though they are a little big for me. I wear glasses and they are comfortable around the ears with them on however I do have to occasionally adjust on the nose because they shift around a bit (probably because the headphones are a little big). Overall I really like these headphones and hope they last for a long time!

reviews.reviewTitle: Super Stylish & Great Sound for the price! 🎧
reviews.reviewText: Noise Cancellation (🌟🌟🌟🌟❌)-I’ll give noise cancellation a 4/5 stars, bits of sound tends to leak if played at higher volumes-For the price point and style, this is still a very good buy!Sound Quality (🌟🌟🌟🌟❌)- Quality is very basic and gets the job done-There doesn’t seem to be an “it” factor to it, but that’s also great to know that it’s reliable for a balanced sound!Battery Life (🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟)-If I could put down an extra dozen stars, I would! I’ve had these headphones for about 3.5 months now and I’ve had to charge these only 4 times now!-I’m a casual listener, using these solely for commutes to work or for quick outings-A great pair of headphones to distract you from the noisy city subways!
